<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,1895,2030]" lastBlockId="37.[151,1437,153,287]" lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="38" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,269,1896,1922]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Remarks:</emphasis>
There is a single record of Buff-banded Rail 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus, 1766)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1766" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1766" box="[782,1279,1895,1922]" class="Aves" family="Rallidae" genus="Hypotaenidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gruiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="philippensis">
<emphasis box="[782,1077,1896,1922]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Hypotaenidia philippensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C. von" box="[1092,1271,1895,1922]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" refId="ref49570" refString="Linnaeus, C. von (1766) Systema Naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. 12 th Edition. Laurentii Salvii, Holmiae (Stockholm), 532 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 68927" type="book" year="1766">Linnaeus, 1766</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, a male killed at Champ des Mars, near 
<collectingRegion box="[435,556,1931,1958]" country="Mauritius" name="Port Louis" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Port Louis</collectingRegion>
, in 1863 and held at UMZC, but the month is not known (
<bibRefCitation author="Rountree, R. R. G. &amp; Guerin, R. &amp; Pelte, S. &amp; Vinson, J." pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="155 - 217" refId="ref54645" refString="Rountree, R. R. G., Guerin, R., Pelte, S. &amp; Vinson, J. (1952) Catalogue of the birds of Mauritius. Mauritius Institute Bulletin, 3, 155 - 217." type="journal article" year="1952">
Rountree 
<emphasis box="[1310,1359,1932,1958]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">et al</emphasis>
. 1952: 180
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Benson, C. W." box="[209,417,1968,1994]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="168 - 172" refId="ref42185" refString="Benson, C. W. (1970) The Cambridge collection from the Malagasy Region. Bulletin of the British Ornithologists' Club, 90 (1), 168 - 172." type="journal article" year="1970">Benson 1970: 171</bibRefCitation>
). E. 
<bibRefCitation author="Newton, E." box="[470,699,1967,1994]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="548 - 554" refId="ref52454" refString="Newton, E. (1888) List of birds of the Mascarene Islands, including the Seychelles (Appendix to the President's address). Transactions of the Norfolk and Norwich Naturalists' Society, 4, 548 - 554." type="journal article" year="1888">Newton (1888: 552)</bibRefCitation>
listed it as accidental, and the genus has not been recorded again in the Mascarenes, or anywhere else in the Indian Ocean (
<bibRefCitation author="Safford, R. J. &amp; Hawkins, A. F. A." box="[817,1112,2003,2030]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" refId="ref54791" refString="Safford, R. J. &amp; Hawkins, A. F. A. (2013) The birds of Africa. Volume VIII. The Malagasy Region. Christopher Helm, London, 1024 pp." type="book" year="2013">Safford &amp; Hawkins 2013</bibRefCitation>
). Benson considered it to be the race 
<emphasis box="[247,345,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">australis</emphasis>
(now synonymised under 
<emphasis box="[644,788,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">H. p. mellori</emphasis>
(Taylor &amp; van Perlo 1998)), but noted that the individual was heavily worn, with most of the feathers of the crown and rump missing and the wings incomplete. If a genuine vagrant, it is a unique and extremely rare one, as the nearest source populations of 
<emphasis box="[1070,1239,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">H. philippensis</emphasis>
are the Moluccas and eastern Australia (Taylor &amp; van Perlo 1998).
</paragraph>
